# fusion-box wine patch 0012
# winewayland.drv: promote patch 0006 vsub children to own
# wayland-backed shm_buffer + attach-child's-own-buffer flush path.
#
# Requires patch 0011 (the driver-interface query).
#
# Problem this fixes:
# Patch 0006's older "attach TOPLEVEL's shm_buffer with wp_viewport crop"
# path breaks whenever Fusion's layout change disrupts Qt's child→toplevel
# DIB merge chain. Reproducers:
#   1. Data Panel toggle: opens/closes push the navbar to a new
#      parent-local position; the parent's shm_buffer at the crop
#      coords no longer contains the toolbar pixels (they got painted
#      into an intermediate widget's DIB that isn't merged all the way
#      up). Result: partial toolbar with white where the rest should be.
#   2. Launch to smaller secondary monitor: Fusion fires ~6 parent
#      commits total before going quiescent; if Qt hadn't painted the
#      toolbar by then, the vsub stays showing an empty (black) region
#      forever.
#
# Fix:
# Attach the CHILD's OWN shm_buffer directly to the wl_subsurface (no
# crop, no dependence on the parent's DIB state). Requires wine to give
# the child a driver-provided window_surface, gated by patch 0011's
# pShouldPromoteChildSurface hook.
#
# Implementation:
#   - WAYLAND_ShouldPromoteChildSurface(hwnd): replicates patch 0006's
#     eligibility check (WS_CHILD + toolbar-sized + toplevel-with-wayland-
#     surface + no own client_surface). NOT gated on WS_VISIBLE because
#     wine calls this from WindowPosChanging, before the style has been
#     updated for the incoming SetWindowPos change — SWP_SHOWWINDOW handling
#     downstream in wine's else-if chain reaches the right decision if we
#     return TRUE here.
#   - Registered as .pShouldPromoteChildSurface in waylanddrv_funcs.
#   - set_window_surface_contents: for any SUBSURFACE-role surface
#     matching the promotion eligibility (toolbar-shaped WS_CHILD), (a)
#     update wl_subsurface_set_position from the current Win32 rects
#     each flush — wine's own wayland_surface_reconfigure_subsurface
#     path is gated by processing.serial and only fires once per
#     xdg-config cycle, which never re-triggers for pure position
#     shifts, so we own the position update path; (b) install an empty
#     input region on the wl_surface so clicks fall through to the
#     toplevel wl_surface (wine's Win32 cursor-position routing finds
#     the toolbar HWND correctly there — without empty input the
#     subsurface claims events but downstream WM message queueing
#     never fires, empirically zero WM_LBUTTONDOWN reaches Qt).
#   - Also: SKIP the old parent-crop iteration in the toplevel's
#     set_window_surface_contents for children with virtual_toplevel
#     set. Their own-buffer flush path now covers rendering; running
#     both would race and let the parent-crop overwrite the child's
#     own commit.
#
# Iteration history in this session:
#   - Initial attempt: checked data->virtual_buffer to gate the
#     position update. Wrong — patch 0006 clears virtual_buffer=FALSE
#     when the promoted child hits wayland_win_data_create_wayland_surface
#     (the normal wine path, not the vsub CREATED path). Fixed by
#     checking role + toolbar-shaped size instead.
#   - Second attempt: my set_position + no input-region change.
#     Position correct but zero WM messages queued for the toolbar.
#     Added empty input region.
#   - Third attempt: dropped my set_position (thought wine's internal
#     path was sufficient). Position regressed — wine's own path fires
#     once and doesn't reapply, so pure-position shifts don't update.
#     Restored my set_position on every flush.
#   - Current: set_position from every flush + empty input region on
#     every flush + skip parent-crop iteration for virtual_toplevel
#     children.
#
# Verified 2026-07-02 on Fusion 360 with fresh container + fresh
# wineprefix: navbar renders at correct bottom-center, click routing
# works, Data Panel toggle no longer breaks it.
#
# Author: fusion-box (claude-code session, with Barrett Otte)
#

--- a/dlls/winewayland.drv/waylanddrv.h	2026-07-03 20:34:36.457595926 -0400
